flavorText: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.
Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.
Many live on mountain trails and remain half buried while keeping an eye on climbers.
They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.
Its feathers, which fall off as it grows, are thin and sharp. In times long past, warriors used them as swords.
They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.
It forcefully squirts water. The water jet never misses prey even if the REMORAID is deep in the sea.
It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face, but it can't help grinning if anyone pats its head.
Because its genetic makeup is irregular, it quickly changes its form due to a variety of causes.
It can't fly yet and must wait until its wings have developed more. Since it's still at a playful age, it hops around friskily.
Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves fell close to anyone other than their Trainers.
It usually murmurs but starts crying loudly if it senses danger. It stops when its ear covers are shut.
It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.
It marks time precisely. Some countries consider it to be a wise friend, versed in the world's ways.
Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.
They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.
It runs through the narrow tunnels formed by Excadrill and Onix. It uses its sharp claws to catch prey.
This Pokémon is said to be a male evolution of Cosmog. At the activation of its third eye, it departs for another world.
It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.
There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.
They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.
These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.
On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose.
It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.
It makes a nest out of the bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.
Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they've been fighting.
It loves to sneak up on people late at night, then startle them with its shrieklike cry.
It's feared as a ghost of the forest. Lumberjacks bring along Fire types, which Trevenant hates, when they enter the forest.
The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.
If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.
Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.
It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.
Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.
It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.
They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.
It shouts loudly by inhaling air, and then using its well-developed stomach muscles to exhale.
They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.
Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speeds to stay airborne.
It circles in the sky, keeping a keen eye out for Pokémon in a weakened state. Its choicest food is Cubone.
Its tongue is just like a human's. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.
They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.
Its adorable behavior and appearance make it popular with men and women, young and old. Its numbers are few, however.
When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.
If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.
When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.
A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.
They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.
Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.
Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.
It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.
It can hover is one spot by flapping its wings at high speed. It flits about to guard its territory.
It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.
With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.
When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.
Its heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.
When it travels underground, it causes rumbling and tremors. It can move at 50 mph.
Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.
It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.
It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.
This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.
A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.
When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.
Its long tongue, slathered with a gooey saliva, sticks to anything, so it is very useful.
It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.
It raises its pincers with eyelike markings for intimidation. It also swings them down dangerously.
As it grows older, its white tail changes colors and splits into six different tails. Its body radiates a faint warmth.
Able to conceal itself in shadows, it never appears before humans, so its very existence was the stuff of myth.
It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.
Its auditory sense is astounding. It has a radar-like ability to understand its surrounding through slight sounds.
These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.
A plan was recently announced to gather many Pikachu and make an electric power plant.
Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything flat in moments.
Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.
Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.
They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.
It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.
It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.
It lives in areas of limited rainfall. When danger approaches, it curls up into a ball to protect its soft stomach.
They don't like to reveal themselves in front of people. They live quietly in packs deep in the mountains.
This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.
It is often seen holding its head in its paws, as if it were suffering from a headache.
It is said that kids who drink Miltank's milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.
It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.
Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.
It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.
Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.
It is called the "Mirage Pokémon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.
The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.
A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.
About an hour after birth, its fiery mane and tail grow out, giving it an impressive appearance.
Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speed of over 180 mph.
It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.
These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.
These intelligent Pokémon touch horns with each other to share information between them.
Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.
Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.
To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and as sticky as cotton candy.
It unleashes psychic power from the orb on its forehead. When its power is exhausted, the orb grows dull and dark.
Its growls make its opponents uneasy. This laid-back Pokémon tends to sleep half the day.
When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.
It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.
It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.
Although it's a quiet, lonely Pokémon, if you try to look at what's under its rag, it will become agitated and resist violently.
With magnetic traction, it pulls its opponents in close. When they're in range, it slashes them with its rear claws.
Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
Two bodies comprise a fixed pair. They spin around each other to generate energy.
Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it's merciless to intruders that enter its territory.
It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.
It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.
A new Pokémon species, rumored to be from the sun. It gives off light while spinning.
It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.
The long hair around its face provides an amazing radar that lets it sense subtle changes in its surroundings.
The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.
From the slight twitches of its bamboo leaf, it deduces its opponent's movements. It's eager to tussle but kindhearted toward its companions.
After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. It powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.
It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.
It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
